comment: RATR shows that Teague (ATL) makes incidental contact with Paul's (LAC) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.

[Incidental or immaterial] Millsap (ATL) sets the hand-off screen for Teague (ATL) on his trailing defender Paul (LAC) without giving him enough room to avoid the screen, however the defenders Paul and Mbah a Moute (LAC) switch and the contact is deemed immaterial.
Horford (ATL) gathers the ball to end his dribble on his right foot, which is step one. He is permitted one more step to establish his pivot foot.
Horford (ATL) sets the screen on Mbah a Moute (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jordan (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Teague's (ATL) drive and shot attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Teague.
Johnson (LAC) sets the screen on Bazemore (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Horford (ATL) and Redick (LAC) briefly engage and separate.
R-SLA and RHH show that Redick (LAC) makes contact with Korver's (ATL) arm while he is dribbling, however the contact does not affect his RSBQ or shot.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Korver (ATL) was behind the three point line on his shot attempt was confirmed.
[Observable in enhanced video] After making the pass, Paul (LAC) grabs Horford (ATL) around the waist and pulls him to the floor affecting his ability to defend.
Korver (ATL) sets the screen on Mbah a Moute (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Korver (ATL) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Redick (LAC) makes incidental contact with Bazemore (ATL) that does not affect his FOM away from the ball.
Redick (LAC) establishes a legal guarding position outside of the restricted area prior to the start of Millsap's (ATL) upward shooting motion and legally contests the layup attempt.
Sefolosha (ATL) commits a take foul on Crawford (LAC).
Redick (LAC) commits a take foul on Horford (ATL).
LHH and LATR show that Teague (ATL) makes incidental contact with Paul's (LAC) arms as he attempts to catch the inbound pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Paul (LAC) prior to going OOB was confirmed.
Mbah a Moute (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends and contests Millsap's (ATL) drive and layup attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Paul (LAC) grabs and holds Teague's (ATL) arm affecting his FOM.
